# ThamOS X — Desktop Environment Upgrade: Full Project Briefing

## Project Context

ThamOS 6 (T6) is an existing, fully functional React + TypeScript + Supabase threat intelligence web application. It currently has three UI themes: "tactical" (GUI dashboard with sidebar navigation), "terminal" (full CRT terminal with CLI commands), and "mission-control" (command palette driven). The codebase is mature with authentication, edge functions for 6+ threat intel APIs, user API key management, scan history, case notes, news feeds, watchlists, alerts, and an admin panel.

**This upgrade adds a fourth theme: "desktop" — a browser-native hacker workstation OS that transforms T6 from a threat intel scanner into a complete hacker workshop environment.** The scanner becomes one app among many running inside a windowed desktop OS. New capabilities include AI agent integration (Claude, GPT, Gemini), GitHub repo browsing/editing, a multi-agent chat workshop, and a proper window management system.

Think of this as adding a Kali Linux / Parrot OS desktop experience that runs in the browser. Every existing feature still works — they just render inside draggable, resizable windows instead of a fixed layout.

