## WHAT TO BUILD: Desktop Theme

### 1. Window Manager System

Build a reusable window manager that all desktop apps use:

**Window Component** (`components/desktop/DesktopWindow.tsx`):
- Draggable by title bar (mousedown/mousemove/mouseup)
- Resizable from edges and corners (resize handle in bottom-right at minimum)
- Minimize to taskbar (hides window, shows in taskbar as minimized)
- Maximize / restore (double-click title bar or click green traffic light)
- Close (removes window from state)
- Z-index management — clicking a window brings it to front
- macOS-style title bar: red/yellow/green dots on the left, title centered, accent-colored icon
- Minimum size constraint (don't let windows collapse to nothing)
- Window state tracked in a central store/context

**Snap Zones**:
- Drag to left edge → snap to left 50%
- Drag to right edge → snap to right 50%
- Drag to top → maximize
- Drag to corners → snap to 25% quadrant
- Show a semi-transparent preview zone when hovering near edges

**Window Manager Context** (`contexts/DesktopContext.tsx`):
```typescript
interface WindowInstance {
  id: string;
  appId: string;           // which app this is (terminal, scanner, browser, etc.)
  title: string;
  icon: string;
  accentColor: string;
  position: { x: number; y: number };
  size: { width: number; height: number };
  minimized: boolean;
  maximized: boolean;
  zIndex: number;
  workspaceId: number;     // which workspace this window is on
  pinned: boolean;         // visible on all workspaces
}

interface DesktopState {
  windows: Record<string, WindowInstance>;
  activeWindowId: string | null;
  activeWorkspace: number;
  workspaces: number[];    // [1, 2, 3, 4]
}
```

Provide methods: openWindow, closeWindow, minimizeWindow, maximizeWindow, restoreWindow, focusWindow, moveToWorkspace, etc.

