## APP.TSX UPDATE

The existing App.tsx switch on theme gets a new branch:

```typescript
if (theme === 'desktop') {
  return (
    <DesktopProvider>  {/* New context for window management */}
      <DesktopLayout>
        {/* DesktopLayout manages its own windows internally */}
        {/* It doesn't receive children the same way — it opens apps as windows */}
      </DesktopLayout>
    </DesktopProvider>
  );
}
```

Note: The desktop theme works differently from tactical/terminal. Instead of App.tsx rendering page components as children, DesktopLayout manages its own window state and opens app components inside DesktopWindow wrappers based on user actions. The DesktopContext tracks which windows are open and their state.

