## PHASE RECOMMENDATION

While this is a single cohesive upgrade, here is a suggested build order where each phase is functional on its own:

**Phase 1**: Desktop shell (DesktopLayout, DesktopWindow, Taskbar, workspaces, boot sequence, desktop icons, app launcher). Terminal app with all commands. Scanner GUI app rendering existing Scanner inside a window. All existing result pages rendering inside windows. System Monitor. Settings in a window. Theme switching works.

**Phase 2**: AI Workshop app with multi-agent chat, streaming responses, context panel. New Supabase tables (agent_conversations, agent_profiles). New edge function (/agent). New API key fields in Settings for Anthropic/OpenAI/Google. Agent configuration in Settings.

**Phase 3**: GitHub OAuth integration. File Manager app. Browser app with real internal routing and GitHub tab. New edge function (/github).

**Phase 4**: Code Editor with CodeMirror, GitHub read/write, "Ask Agent" feature. Case Manager enhancements (linked scans, linked conversations). Intel Dashboard enhancements.

Build Phase 1 first as it gives the desktop environment its core functionality without requiring any new backend changes. Each subsequent phase adds capabilities that build on the previous.



